          description for ftrace_update_ftrace_func() :
            this function calls twice the function ftrace_call_replace().
            the first once,it need to modify code at position @ftrace_call,
            the label in assembly function @ftrace_caller().
            the second once,is the code at position @ftrace_regs_call,
            which is the label in assembly function @ftrace_regs_caller.
            both functions are defined in <ftrace_64.S>.
            function ftrace_call_replace() is defined in the same file,which
            receives two parameters,@ip and @addr,returns a const char pointer.
            the const char pointer,actually will points to a union member named
            @text,the union object is static linkage,declared in text_gen_insn(),
            whose type is "union text_poke_insn".
            @ip is the rip position where code need to be modified,@addr is
            the jump to address or call to address.
            if ftrace_is_jmp() on @addr is true,ftrace_jmp_get() will be called
            on @addr to get address that suit for "jmp" instruction,then
            invoke text_gen_insn(),pass it JMP32_INSN_OPCODE flag,@ip,and the
            new address suit for "jmp",to create machine code corresponding to
            "jmp" instruction.
            if @addr is not a "jmp" address,then CALL_INSN_OPCODE flag is passed
            to text_gen_insn(),@ip and @addr remain unchanged,to create machine
            code corresponding to "call" instruction.
            after ftrace_call_replace() returned,ftrace_update_ftrace_func()
            invoke smp_text_poke_single() to install single instruction to
            the expected position(@ip points to),of course,the MCOUNT_INSN_SIZE
            need to be considered.(once ftrace_call_replace() returned,call once
            smp_text_poke_single())

